00:37:10,500 --> 00:37:12,060
In the Qing army,

586
00:37:12,460 --> 00:37:13,710
soldiers cut queue

587
00:37:13,790 --> 00:37:14,830
to train,

588
00:37:15,100 --> 00:37:17,060
but when have we ever
seen an officer do it?

589
00:37:17,060 --> 00:37:19,230
Yes, exactly!

590
00:37:22,350 --> 00:37:24,080
What are you all arguing about?

591
00:37:24,460 --> 00:37:25,750
Duke Liang from the Imperial Guards

592
00:37:25,750 --> 00:37:27,610
has also cut off his queue, right?

593
00:37:27,620 --> 00:37:28,670
Empress Cixi saw it

594
00:37:28,670 --> 00:37:30,190
and didn't say anything about it.

595
00:37:30,190 --> 00:37:31,230
I've also heard

596
00:37:31,540 --> 00:37:33,270
Commander Yang and Duke Liang

597
00:37:33,270 --> 00:37:35,530
were classmates when studying in Japan.

598
00:37:36,270 --> 00:37:37,790
So they have a connection?

599
00:37:37,790 --> 00:37:38,350
Yes.

600
00:37:38,820 --> 00:37:39,460
Everyone,

601
00:37:40,060 --> 00:37:41,670
we need to be more cautious in the future.

602
00:37:41,670 --> 00:37:42,790
He and Duke Liang

603
00:37:42,790 --> 00:37:44,910
are very close.

604
00:37:47,910 --> 00:37:49,060
Everyone, stand up!

605
00:37:52,620 --> 00:37:56,150
The new commander-in-chief
of the Sixth Division has arrived.

606
00:38:15,540 --> 00:38:16,540
Sit down!

607
00:38:27,940 --> 00:38:28,910
Officers of the Sixth Division

608
00:38:28,910 --> 00:38:30,640
have a peculiar way of smiling.

609
00:38:31,500 --> 00:38:33,700
They hide daggers behind their smiles.

610
00:38:36,580 --> 00:38:38,270
When I set off from Beijing,

611
00:38:39,750 --> 00:38:41,310
a friend of mine introduced

612
00:38:41,310 --> 00:38:42,640
the Sixth Division to me

613
00:38:43,270 --> 00:38:44,330
in just four words:

614
00:38:45,350 --> 00:38:47,010
"Good horses, sharp swords."

615
00:38:48,230 --> 00:38:49,710
Yesterday and today,

616
00:38:50,310 --> 00:38:51,460
General Zhou and I,

617
00:38:51,310 --> 00:38:53,780
[The 12th brigade of the Sixth Division,
Brigade Commander Zhou]

618
00:38:51,980 --> 00:38:53,310
along with General Wu,

619
00:38:53,940 --> 00:38:56,350
we visited some units
of the Sixth Division.

620
00:38:54,930 --> 00:38:58,080
[The 11th brigade of the Sixth Division,
Brigade Commander Wu]

621
00:38:56,790 --> 00:38:58,520
They truly lived up to the name.

622
00:38:58,790 --> 00:39:00,500
The cavalry battalion
of the Sixth Division

623
00:39:00,500 --> 00:39:01,700
has fine horse breeds

624
00:39:01,790 --> 00:39:03,520
and outstanding sword skills.

625
00:39:03,540 --> 00:39:05,190
I had a pleasant conversation

626
00:39:05,190 --> 00:39:07,730
with the officers and soldiers
of the cavalry battalion.

627
00:39:07,730 --> 00:39:08,840
The new commander-in-chief

628
00:39:08,840 --> 00:39:10,480
used to be

629
00:39:11,580 --> 00:39:14,020
the Director of Cavalry
at the Ministry of War.

630
00:39:14,020 --> 00:39:15,830
So the first thing he did after arriving

631
00:39:15,830 --> 00:39:17,690
was visit the cavalry battalion.

632
00:39:18,110 --> 00:39:19,470
Director of Cavalry?

633
00:39:19,910 --> 00:39:21,440
That's not a high position.

634
00:39:21,750 --> 00:39:25,680
He's Duke Liang's classmate.
He must come from a powerful background.

635
00:39:26,310 --> 00:39:27,020
Indeed.

636
00:39:27,670 --> 00:39:28,750
I asked

637
00:39:28,750 --> 00:39:30,810
a sergeant in the cavalry battalion,

638
00:39:30,940 --> 00:39:31,830
I said,

639
00:39:32,580 --> 00:39:33,710
"Have you ever heard of

640
00:39:33,710 --> 00:39:34,870
a poem from Britain,

641
00:39:35,830 --> 00:39:37,560
specifically about cavalry?"

642
00:39:38,270 --> 00:39:39,500
He said, "What poem?

643
00:39:39,980 --> 00:39:41,910
Please, Sir, let me know about it."

644
00:39:42,190 --> 00:39:43,140
So,

645
00:39:43,390 --> 00:39:44,540
I recited this

646
00:39:44,540 --> 00:39:45,940
English doggerel to him.

647
00:39:46,270 --> 00:39:47,070
The poem goes:

648
00:39:47,940 --> 00:39:50,500
"For want of a nail the shoe was lost;

649
00:39:51,060 --> 00:39:53,790
for want of a shoe the horse was lost;

650
00:39:54,270 --> 00:39:56,910
and for want of a horse the rider was lost;

651
00:39:57,270 --> 00:39:59,910
for want of a rider the battle was lost;

652
00:40:00,350 --> 00:40:02,980
for want of a battle the kingdom was lost.

653
00:40:04,060 --> 00:40:05,350
And all for

654
00:40:06,100 --> 00:40:07,760
the want of a horseshoe nail."

655
00:40:08,910 --> 00:40:10,310
What kind of poem is this?

656
00:40:10,390 --> 00:40:10,940
Is it really necessary?

657
00:40:10,940 --> 00:40:12,600
Can this even be called a poem?

658
00:40:15,710 --> 00:40:16,460
I know

659
00:40:17,460 --> 00:40:18,140
everyone here

660
00:40:18,140 --> 00:40:19,980
might think it sounds a bit over the top.

661
00:40:19,980 --> 00:40:21,270
But there's

662
00:40:21,270 --> 00:40:22,870
one thing we can take from it.

663
00:40:23,460 --> 00:40:24,460
That is...

664
00:40:25,620 --> 00:40:27,190
every small detail

665
00:40:27,190 --> 00:40:29,230
of a soldier's life

666
00:40:29,790 --> 00:40:31,100
could be related to

667
00:40:31,130 --> 00:40:32,460
the fate of the country.

668
00:40:32,980 --> 00:40:34,750
Now the country is in danger,

669
00:40:35,420 --> 00:40:36,540
we soldiers

670
00:40:36,540 --> 00:40:37,870
must work twice as hard,

671
00:40:38,580 --> 00:40:39,730
so we don't

672
00:40:39,930 --> 00:40:41,530
let down our people's trust.

673
00:40:41,940 --> 00:40:43,270
We must always remember

674
00:40:43,580 --> 00:40:44,700
a strong army

675
00:40:45,390 --> 00:40:46,920
is the backbone of a nation.

676
00:40:56,670 --> 00:41:01,710
-Bravo!
-Bravo!
